{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_18","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' Body-Tell/reports/26-05-24/runs/SP-A.P0/audit_voxtell_alignment.html\"","aggregated_output":"<!doctype html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>SP-A.P0 VoxTell Alignment Audit</title>\n  <style>\n    body { font: 15px/1.55 -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \"Segoe UI\", sans-serif; margin: 0; color: #17202a; background: #f6f8fa; }\n    main { max-width: 1160px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 32px 24px 56px; }\n    section { background: #fff; border: 1px solid #d8e0e7; border-radius: 8px; padding: 18px 20px; margin: 16px 0; }\n    h1 { margin: 0 0 6px; font-size: 28px; }\n    h2 { margin: 0 0 10px; font-size: 20px; }\n    table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; margin: 10px 0; font-size: 14px; }\n    th, td { border: 1px solid #d8e0e7; padding: 8px 10px; text-align: left; vertical-align: top; }\n    th { background: #eef3f7; }\n    code, pre { font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace; }\n    code { background: #edf3f7; border-radius: 4px; padding: 1px 4px; }\n    pre { overflow-x: auto; background: #111827; color: #f8fafc; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px; }\n    .meta { color: #5d6875; }\n    .warn { border-left: 4px solid #9a4a17; background: #fff7ed; padding: 10px 12px; }\n    .ok { border-left: 4px solid #276749; background: #eef9f0; padding: 10px 12px; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<main>\n  <header>\n    <h1>SP-A.P0 VoxTell Compatibility Baseline Audit</h1>\n    <p class=\"meta\">Body config: <code>/home/xiaoqingguo/Rongkun/code/Hyper-Tell/Body-Tell/configs/phase1_voxtell_body.yaml</code>; VoxTell profile: <code>/home/xiaoqingguo/Rongkun/code/Hyper-Tell/VoxTell/models-weight/voxtell/voxtell_v1.1</code>.</p>\n  </header>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Projection Shape Baseline</h2>\n    <p><strong>Body-Tell current</strong>: <code>num_heads=32</code>, actual fused projection stages <code>4</code> from configured <code>5</code>; prefix is <code>mask_projections</code>, target aligned prefix is <code>project_to_decoder_channels</code>.</p>\n    <table><thead><tr><th>Stage</th><th>Channels</th><th>Output dim</th><th>Final linear weight</th><th>Key</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>0</td><td>32</td><td>32</td><td>(32, 2048)</td><td>mask_projections.0.2</td></tr>\n<tr><td>1</td><td>64</td><td>2048</td><td>(2048, 2048)</td><td>mask_projections.1.2</td></tr>\n<tr><td>2</td><td>128</td><td>4096</td><td>(4096, 2048)</td><td>mask_projections.2.2</td></tr>\n<tr><td>3</td><td>256</td><td>8192</td><td>(8192, 2048)</td><td>mask_projections.3.2</td></tr></tbody></table>\n    <p><strong>VoxTell source default</strong>: <code>num_heads=1</code>. This is the class default in <code>voxtell_model.py</code>, not necessarily the shipped v1.1 checkpoint profile.</p>\n    <table><thead><tr><th>Stage</th><th>Channels</th><th>Output dim</th><th>Final linear weight</th><th>Key</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>0</td><td>32</td><td>32</td><td>(32, 432)</td><td>project_to_decoder_channels.0.2</td></tr>\n<tr><td>1</td><td>64</td><td>64</td><td>(64, 432)</td><td>project_to_decoder_channels.1.2</td></tr>\n<tr><td>2</td><td>128</td><td>128</td><td>(128, 432)</td><td>project_to_decoder_channels.2.2</td></tr>\n<tr><td>3</td><td>256</td><td>256</td><td>(256, 432)</td><td>project_to_decoder_channels.3.2</td></tr>\n<tr><td>4</td><td>320</td><td>320</td><td>(320, 432)</td><td>project_to_decoder_channels.4.2</td></tr></tbody></table>\n    <p><strong>VoxTell v1.1 checkpoint-derived</strong>: predictor override <code>num_heads=32</code>; checkpoint inferred <code>num_heads=32</code>; pos_embed shape <code>(1728, 1, 2048)</code>.</p>\n    <table><thead><tr><th>Stage</th><th>Channels</th><th>Output dim</th><th>Final linear weight</th><th>Key</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>0</td><td>32</td><td>32</td><td>(32, 2048)</td><td>project_to_decoder_channels.0.2</td></tr>\n<tr><td>1</td><td>64</td><td>2048</td><td>(2048, 2048)</td><td>project_to_decoder_channels.1.2</td></tr>\n<tr><td>2</td><td>128</td><td>4096</td><td>(4096, 2048)</td><td>project_to_decoder_channels.2.2</td></tr>\n<tr><td>3</td><td>256</td><td>8192</td><td>(8192, 2048)</td><td>project_to_decoder_channels.3.2</td></tr>\n<tr><td>4</td><td>320</td><td>10240</td><td>(10240, 2048)</td><td>project_to_decoder_channels.4.2</td></tr></tbody></table>\n    <p class=\"warn\">Audit finding: the model class default is <code>num_heads=1</code>, but the v1.1 predictor and checkpoint metadata use <code>num_heads=32</code>. P4/P6 should key off the actual checkpoint being loaded.</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Weight-Key Audit Input</h2>\n    <p>Current Body-Tell can only directly reuse same-name/same-shape subsets before SP-A architecture work. This table is a baseline input for P6, not a claim that current Body-Tell is already checkpoint-compatible.</p>\n    <table><thead><tr><th>Prefix</th><th>Body keys</th><th>Checkpoint keys</th><th>Same-name shape-compatible</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>decoder</code></td><td>32</td><td>508</td><td>0</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>encoder</code></td><td>30</td><td>448</td><td>0</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>mask_projections</code></td><td>16</td><td>0</td><td>0</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>pos_embed</code></td><td>0</td><td>1</td><td>0</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>project_bottleneck_embed</code></td><td>0</td><td>4</td><td>0</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>project_text_embed</code></td><td>4</td><td>4</td><td>4</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>project_to_decoder_channels</code></td><td>0</td><td>20</td><td>0</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>project_visual_embed</code></td><td>4</td><td>0</td><td>0</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>transformer_decoder</code></td><td>110</td><td>110</td><td>110</td></tr></tbody></table>\n    <p>Same-name compatible current Body-Tell keys: <code>114</code>; shape mismatches: <code>0</code>; checkpoint keys unexpected to current Body-Tell: <code>981</code>.</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>P6 Whitelist Input</h2>\n    <h3>Required exact skips</h3>\n    <table><thead><tr><th>Pattern</th><th>Reason</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>pos_embed</code></td><td>Body-Tell current non-192^3 crop uses dynamic positional encoding.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n    <h3>Conditional skips</h3>\n    <table><thead><tr><th>Pattern</th><th>Reason</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>project_to_decoder_channels.[1-4].*, decoder.transpconvs.[1-4].*, decoder.seg_layers.*</code></td><td>only apply if loading a checkpoint generated from the VoxTellModel source default num_heads=1 into a Body-Tell num_heads=32 model</td></tr></tbody></table>\n    <ul><li>checkpoint-derived num_heads matches Body-Tell current num_heads; do not skip project_to_decoder_channels.* or decoder mask-fusion keys for this reason</li></ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section>\n    <h2>Machine-Readable Audit Payload</h2>\n    <pre>{\n  &quot;body&quot;: {\n    &quot;config_path&quot;: &quot;/home/xiaoqingguo/Rongkun/code/Hyper-Tell/Body-Tell/configs/phase1_voxtell_body.yaml&quot;,\n    &quot;encoder_channels&quot;: [\n      32,\n      64,\n      128,\n      256,\n      320\n    ],\n    &quot;fused_stage_count_actual&quot;: 4,\n    &quot;num_heads&quot;: 32,\n    &quot;num_maskformer_stages_config&quot;: 5,\n    &quot;projection_prefix&quot;: &quot;mask_projections&quot;,\n    &quot;projection_rows&quot;: [\n      {\n        &quot;bias_shape&quot;: [\n          32\n        ],\n        &quot;channels&quot;: 32,\n        &quot;key&quot;: &quot;mask_projections.0.2&quot;,\n        &quot;output_dim&quot;: 32,\n        &quot;stage&quot;: 0,\n        &quot;target_key&quot;: &quot;project_to_decoder_channels.0.2&quot;,\n        &quot;weight_shape&quot;: [\n          32,\n          2048\n        ]\n      },\n      {\n        &quot;bias_shape&quot;: [\n          2048\n        ],\n        &quot;channels&quot;: 64,\n        &quot;key&quot;: &quot;mask_projections.1.2&quot;,\n        &quot;output_d